# Optional fleet /etc/hosts entries for your Kintsugi USB build.
#
# The PUBLIC toolkit ships with NO fleet hosts baked in. To bake your own
# fleet's hostnames into a build (and have first-boot re-add them), create:
#
#   config/includes.chroot/etc/kintsugi/fleet-hosts
#
# with one "<IP>  <hostname>" per line. That path is git-ignored, so your
# private topology never lands in the public repo. live-build copies it to
# /etc/kintsugi/fleet-hosts in the image; build-custom-iso.sh (build time) and
# first-boot-setup.sh (boot time) append it to /etc/hosts.
#
# Example contents (replace with your own):
# 10.0.0.10  myhost-a
# 10.0.0.11  myhost-b
